= Gender Recognition Reform (Scotland) Bill

The Scottish Parliament is to debate an <span style="color: #cbc48a;">**SNP**</span> bill to simplify the process of changing legal gender for transgender people. Despite being tabled by the SNP, the party is likely to face some resistance on the issue by its conservative wing, while the <span style="color: #3072b5;">Scottish Tories</span> are outright hostile to the proposal.

We could support the bill. However the matter of transgender rights is becoming increasingly controversial both in Scotland and the rest of Britain.

