Labour MSPs are split on the issue, with most abstaining. Only a few of our MSPs either vote for or against the motion. Despite the <span style="color: #cbc48a;">SNP</span> facing a rebelion and <span style="color: #3072b5;">Tory</span> opposition, the bill passes without our support. Only the <span style="color: #50bd47;">Scottish Greens</span> and <span style:"color: #f2c514;">Lib Dems</span> were united in support, and our left flank consider us to have ingored transgender people.  
